{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01N2UF8j7PA16ripznXwge7z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012q9vCYbGV3LbV2pZvTNrDV","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/store.go.md","content":"Purpose: Thread-safe in-memory store for frontend user interaction events, with Add and List operations.\nDesigned to be embedded in an HTTP service that records and retrieves events concurrently.\n\nTags: implementation, store\n\n## Key types\n\n**Event** — the data model for a single user interaction. Fields `ID`, `Type`, `UserID`, and `Payload` map directly to the JSON API contract via struct tags.\n\n**EventStore** — holds a `sync.RWMutex` and a `[]Event` slice. The mutex gates all reads and writes.\n\n## Main functions\n\n**NewEventStore** — returns a zero-value `*EventStore`. The slice starts nil but is initialised lazily by `append`.\n\n**Add** — takes a write lock, generates a UUID v4 via `github.com/google/uuid`, appends the event, and returns the stored copy. UUID generation happens outside the lock — only the append is protected — keeping the critical section minimal.\n\n**List** — takes a read lock and copies the slice via `make`+`copy`, guaranteeing callers receive a snapshot that cannot be modified by concurrent writes. Returns `[]Event{}` (never nil) so JSON encoding produces `[]` rather than `null`.\n\n## Design decisions\n\n- `sync.RWMutex` chosen over `sync.Mutex` because reads are expected to dominate; concurrent `GET /events` calls share the read lock without blocking each other.\n- The return slice is initialised with `make([]Event, len(s.events))` before `copy` rather than `append(nil, s.events...)` to make the non-nil guarantee explicit and the intent clear.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":214,"cache_read_input_tokens":25908,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":214},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab3e3de6-ad15-4c06-aec8-1b2f8934ce06","uuid":"6e6eaad4-5496-4e72-8e3a-c6ca13b19232"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012q9vCYbGV3LbV2pZvTNrDV","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/store.go.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab3e3de6-ad15-4c06-aec8-1b2f8934ce06","uuid":"a62ac011-0d43-4ad7-ba70-767f9409a25a","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:09:44.859Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/store.go.md","content":"Purpose: Thread-safe in-memory store for frontend user interaction events, with Add and List operations.\nDesigned to be embedded in an HTTP service that records and retrieves events concurrently.\n\nTags: implementation, store\n\n## Key types\n\n**Event** — the data model for a single user interaction. Fields `ID`, `Type`, `UserID`, and `Payload` map directly to the JSON API contract via struct tags.\n\n**EventStore** — holds a `sync.RWMutex` and a `[]Event` slice. The mutex gates all reads and writes.\n\n## Main functions\n\n**NewEventStore** — returns a zero-value `*EventStore`. The slice starts nil but is initialised lazily by `append`.\n\n**Add** — takes a write lock, generates a UUID v4 via `github.com/google/uuid`, appends the event, and returns the stored copy. UUID generation happens outside the lock — only the append is protected — keeping the critical section minimal.\n\n**List** — takes a read lock and copies the slice via `make`+`copy`, guaranteeing callers receive a snapshot that cannot be modified by concurrent writes. Returns `[]Event{}` (never nil) so JSON encoding produces `[]` rather than `null`.\n\n## Design decisions\n\n- `sync.RWMutex` chosen over `sync.Mutex` because reads are expected to dominate; concurrent `GET /events` calls share the read lock without blocking each other.\n- The return slice is initialised with `make([]Event, len(s.events))` before `copy` rather than `append(nil, s.events...)` to make the non-nil guarantee explicit and the intent clear.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A14aN156WCDYmQhV8uc7s7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ByGsfKXajNNvE4ZKv6k7Wh","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/handlers.go.md","content":"Purpose: HTTP handler constructors for the metrics service, implementing POST and GET for the /events endpoint.\nEach constructor closes over an *EventStore and returns an http.HandlerFunc.\n\nTags: implementation, metrics\n\n## Key types\n\n**validEventTypes** — package-level map used as a set for O(1) validation of the `type` field. Accepted values are `\"click-mouse\"` and `\"submit-form\"`.\n\n## Main functions\n\n**PostEvent(store) http.HandlerFunc** — decodes the JSON request body into an anonymous struct, rejects unknown event types with 400, calls `store.Add`, and writes the stored event as 201 JSON. Method is checked first; non-POST returns 405.\n\n**GetEvents(store) http.HandlerFunc** — calls `store.List` and encodes the result as 200 JSON. Non-GET returns 405.\n\n## Design decisions\n\n- Method checks are handled inside each handler (in addition to the mux dispatch in routes.go) so that handlers remain independently testable without the router wrapping them.\n- `json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(stored)` is used rather than `json.Marshal` + `w.Write` to avoid an intermediate buffer allocation.\n- The anonymous decode struct mirrors only the fields the API accepts; clients cannot inject an ID through the request body.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":681,"cache_read_input_tokens":26122,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":681},"output_tokens":63,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab3e3de6-ad15-4c06-aec8-1b2f8934ce06","uuid":"d6a090b8-afa2-464a-b1bf-587a0db777c4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ByGsfKXajNNvE4ZKv6k7Wh","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/handlers.go.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab3e3de6-ad15-4c06-aec8-1b2f8934ce06","uuid":"19a9d704-be45-4edf-b4a1-fb7d5ad41eca","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:09:53.852Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/handlers.go.md","content":"Purpose: HTTP handler constructors for the metrics service, implementing POST and GET for the /events endpoint.\nEach constructor closes over an *EventStore and returns an http.HandlerFunc.\n\nTags: implementation, metrics\n\n## Key types\n\n**validEventTypes** — package-level map used as a set for O(1) validation of the `type` field. Accepted values are `\"click-mouse\"` and `\"submit-form\"`.\n\n## Main functions\n\n**PostEvent(store) http.HandlerFunc** — decodes the JSON request body into an anonymous struct, rejects unknown event types with 400, calls `store.Add`, and writes the stored event as 201 JSON. Method is checked first; non-POST returns 405.\n\n**GetEvents(store) http.HandlerFunc** — calls `store.List` and encodes the result as 200 JSON. Non-GET returns 405.\n\n## Design decisions\n\n- Method checks are handled inside each handler (in addition to the mux dispatch in routes.go) so that handlers remain independently testable without the router wrapping them.\n- `json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(stored)` is used rather than `json.Marshal` + `w.Write` to avoid an intermediate buffer allocation.\n- The anonymous decode struct mirrors only the fields the API accepts; clients cannot inject an ID through the request body.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
